post_text:
The Oaks academy is participating in the Southwest Airlines Adopt-a-Pilot Program. Our students have adopted Mrs. Shults as our pilot and got to meet her this past Friday. They really enjoyed getting to try on flight suits and other flight gear!

Southwest Airlines Pilots such as Mrs. Shults visit classrooms and support teachers in reinforcing the importance of school and how the power of hard work and commitment are essential to achieving dreams. She will lead activities in the Adopt-A-Pilot curriculum by making lessons in Science, Geography, and Math come alive, demonstrating to students how these subjects can be applied in “real life.”
text:

post_text: This year one of our focus areas is to set our students up for success by teaching them the skills they will need upon graduation. We also want to open their eyes to a variety of vocations and career opportunities. We are always looking for people to share with our students about their career choices and experiences. If you would be interested in sharing with our students, please contact us!
